How do I capture two incredible months (October & November 2022) of extended vacation in Brazil 🇧🇷 within a quick edited video?  I never want to forget that my dream to spend my birthday month and beyond in Rio de Janeiro with my actual birthday in the Brazilian Amazon came true.  I lived out my dream of quality time with the macacos, swimming in the Rio Negro, playing with pink dolphins, visiting an indigenous tribe, living in two AirBnB apartments with multiple friends visiting me to stay in Rio.  Exhale.  I’m just so grateful for my time in beautiful Brazil.  I will never forget it as long as I live.  Thank you Framily for making my time so incredible: @marcusbooth845 @skippynyc @taririlodge @andersonlimaeventos @shesfullgrown @therealvogue @wethrivenojo @miguel.xperiencer & quite a few more that I can’t even tag 😜😈😍 Big thanks to @myloveuntitled 🙏🏾🙏🏾🙏🏾 Your love still sustains me to this day. What can I say about three stops of the #renaissanceworldtour but simply MAGICAL, one of the best concert tours I’ve ever witnessed, easily top 5 & y’all know the #concertfreak has been to many.  If you love Renaissance the album, you’re gonna LOVE LOVE this tour with a perfect set list of 36 songs including the entire Renaissance album.  I love when artist do this!  And the mic is ON the entire time… dare I say best in the live concert game for someone who dances as much and dances so well. 

The show is so thoughtful and pro-Black LGBTQ ✊🏾with clear homage to American ballroom culture (and house music) from the paddles doting the number “10” given to VIP attendees who are sure to serve up 10s across the board, to the colors of the black LGBT flag that opens the show, to the intentional unisex bathrooms and the dancers straight from today’s ballroom scene and the picture of Tina Knowles with Beyoncé’s Uncle Johnny who Beyoncé says introduced her to LGBT culture and the music of Renaissance and more.  The show is EVERYTHING it needed to be and worth every bit of the concert ticket. 

My only critique of the show is that the view from Pure Honey on stage B (not as good as A) and neither as good as Beyhive or Gold Circle (A or B) nor many other seats in the house as Beyoncé doesn’t serve any extra attention to the Bad or Money Bitches so for me, if you haven’t bought an on-stage ticket yet: DON’T!  You’ll enjoy the show much more (sound, video visuals, viewpoint) from most other areas/seats in the arena. 

Go ahead and mention Beyoncé with the Greats, the Giants of entertainers: Michael, Prince, Janet, Madonna, Bowie, Tina Turner - Beyoncé is one of the Great entertainers of our time, dare I say one of the Greatest that the world has known.  The Queen delivered!

Yesterday, it was as if God came down and sat right next to me on the plane.  Meet my new friend Gordon.  I gave up my seat 22C to a father who hoped to be seated with his family. This landed me in 32C next to Gordon and his wife who were in 32A & 32B. 

Gordon has been to 131 countries and all 50 states and is still traveling at 89 years young, visiting Yellowstone Park for the first time with his wife.  The conversation was so inspiring that I had to open my phone and start taking notes.  He said to me (amongst so many other nuggets for life): “As long as you have money, time and most important - GOOD HEALTH, Don’t you dare stop traveling young man.  Don’t you dare!” And then he added, “You wanna know the secret to living a long, healthy life?  Adventurous travel!  Keeps you young and vibrant!” 

And this, my friends is what I needed to hear.  This is why I travel.  Thank you Gordon.  I needed our conversation.  It was perfectly placed to support me making a super huge decision I’ve been wrestling with for weeks.  Details SOON! 

#mydreamsareplansworldtour #anthonyantoine #boyfromnewark #travelovereverything

OMG, Is my mic on?  I’m SCREAMING with excitement! 

Celebrate with me FAM!  I’ve held this news since Nov. 2021 when I made my initial down payment and really, wavered on my decision, second-guessed myself for the past few weeks to months.  But after meeting Gordon on the plane to South Dakota a week ago, I buckled down and paid my 2nd and total balance this past Wednesday making it official… 

I AM BOOKED on Royal Carribean’s inaugural Ultimate World Cruise, an epic 274-night adventure that visits all seven continents, more than 150 destinations in 65 countries and 11 great wonders of the world. I’ll be departing Atlanta on December 9th (leaving Miami’s port on December 10th, 2023) & not returning until September 10th, 2024 - literally 9 months on a cruise ship traveling the world.  This will be my ultimate solo trip with the intention of going on a spiritual journey, really making this THE definitive trip of my lifetime. 

Back in the day, Michael and I initially didn’t think we would like cruising but eventually took 6 cruises together, falling in love with the cruise experience.  It’s the best, most economical way to get a snapshot of many countries within the shortest amount of time.  You meet so many different people, the excursions are thrilling and adventurous, it’s really a great way to travel.  I explicitly remember asking Husboo after our first cruise, “Who gets to stay on a cruise for months at a time?  Can you imagine?” His reply, “YOU!  One day, it’s you.  I know you.  One day it will be you.” 

And so it is.  Thank God & Husboo for the grace and love that sustains me.  Family & Friends, stay tuned for the celebration send-off in December.  But for now, Celebrate with me FAM!  God willing, I’m soon to travel the world.

Part 1: Traveling while black/white privilege Italy post: 

I drove 68 miles/just shy of 2 hours outside of Rome and landed in this beautiful remote town Manciano, Italy 🇮🇹. I arrived near the address on the paper but I wasn’t totally sure exactly where the unit was.  Soon as I get out of my car, a police car pulls up behind me, both officers looking at me suspect, their car blocking me in the parking space.  I’m not alarmed (I mean, it’s not AMERICA 🇺🇸😩) and decide to ask them if they know the address I have saved as a picture on my phone.  They look at the address, speak to each other in Italian and now ask for my documents. “Dov'è il tuo documento,” “Documento!” 

FULL STORY ON MY FACEBOOk PAGE/link in bio. 

Listen, any exchange with police in America, I’m immediately here.  Somehow, I just didn’t expect it in Italy.  As I’m waiting, 2 different people come to the other side and ask the officers a question. They get their question answered and their on their way.  Why couldn’t my exchange be as simple?  Why am I being detained now for over ten minutes?  Can I get my spare battery pack out my car so my phone won’t die?  Both officers have guns.  Will they think I’m retrieving a weapon instead of a battery pack?  I’m traveling alone.  I say to myself, “Anthony, no false moves.” I’m now policing myself.  But why? 

To be continued…
#anthonyantoine 
#travelingwhileblack

Photo of the Day: Today was simply EPIC! 

I made a commitment that with every visit to Rio de Janeiro, my #1 favorite city since 2007, I would visit a new city in Brazil 🇧🇷. Today’s new city was one of Brazil’s national parks Lençóis Maranhenses (Nacional dos Lençóis Maranhenses) in Maranhão state in northeastern Brazil, just east of the Baía de São José. The sand dunes and freshwater lagoons were incredible.  It was like floating in a fluffy dream - here at today’s sunset 08.31.23 at 5:32pm. 

Eu absolutamente amo os Lençóis Maranhenses!

We had a timmmmmmeeeeeeeeee Saturday night 12.2.23.  My 5th annual NYE party came early & doubled as my Bon Voyage party.  The theme: Around the World in a Night with attendees asked to dress representing a beloved country & my family showed out! 

There was so much love & fun in the room.  Again, I feel the richest man alive because in this journey of life, all that truly matters is LOVE!  My family & friends really made a brotha feel so special, loved & supported.  It means the world to me.  Thank you to everyone who attended.  Also, thank you for all the continued messages wishing me well on this incredible journey ahead! 

I leave Atlanta Friday 12.08.23 and our ship sails from Miami 12.10.23.  OMG, this is happening. Let the countdown begin!
